✅ Simple Sentence: The team submitted the proposal.
✅ Compound Sentence: The client approved the design, and we started the development.
✅ Complex Sentence: Since the deadline is approaching, we need to work faster.
________________________________________
3. Subject-Verb Agreement
✅ Singular Subject → Singular Verb
•	The manager approves the budget.
•	The meeting starts at 10 AM.
✅ Plural Subject → Plural Verb
•	The employees attend training sessions every week.
•	The reports are ready for review.
✅ Special Cases:
•	Everyone in the office is working hard.
•	The data needs verification.
________________________________________
4. Tenses (Present, Past, Future – Simple & Continuous)
Tense	Example Sentence (Office Communication)
Present Simple	She handles customer queries efficiently.
Present Continuous	I am working on the quarterly report.
Past Simple	We completed the project last week.
Past Continuous	She was preparing the slides when the meeting started.
Future Simple	They will finalize the budget tomorrow.
Future Continuous	I will be presenting the report at 3 PM.
________________________________________
5. Articles (A, An, The)
✅ I need a laptop for work.
✅ She gave me an update on the project.
✅ We scheduled the meeting for Monday.
________________________________________
6. Prepositions (in, on, at, by, for, etc.)
✅ The meeting is at 2 PM.
✅ The files are in the shared folder.
✅ She is working on the new project.
✅ We need to submit the report by Friday.
________________________________________
7. Conjunctions & Linking Words
✅ I will attend the meeting, but I have another call afterward.
✅ She completed the report because the manager requested it.
✅ We can either schedule the meeting today or postpone it to tomorrow.
________________________________________
8. Question Formation (Yes/No & WH-questions)
✅ Yes/No Questions:
•	Did you complete the task? (Yes/No)
•	Is the report ready? (Yes/No) – No->  // The report is not ready.
✅ WH-questions:
•	What time is the meeting?
•	Where is the client presentation being held?
•	Why was the project delayed?
✅ Polite Office Questions:
•	Could you please send me the report?
•	May I schedule a meeting for tomorrow?
Exercise1:
1. Parts of Speech (Nouns, Verbs, Adjectives, etc.)
Fill in the blanks with the correct word type:
✅ Noun: The _______ (person, place, or thing) was scheduled for tomorrow.
✅ Verb: She _______ (action word) the email before leaving the office.
✅ Adjective: We need a _______ (describing word) report on the client’s feedback.
✅ Adverb: He completed the task _______ (describing how the action happened).
✅ Preposition: The documents are _______ (location word) the table.
✅ Conjunction: I wanted to finish the report on time, _______ I was interrupted.
✅ Pronoun: _______ (he/she/they) will review the contract before signing.
________________________________________
2. Basic Sentence Formation (S + V + O)
Complete the sentences:
✅ Simple Sentence: The team _______ the new project.
✅ Compound Sentence: The meeting started late, _______ we still finished on time.
✅ Complex Sentence: Since the deadline is near, _______ harder to complete the work.
________________________________________
3. Subject-Verb Agreement
Choose the correct verb:
✅ The manager _______ (approve/approves) the budget.
✅ The employees _______ (attend/attends) training every week.
✅ Everyone in the office _______ (is/are) working hard.
________________________________________
4. Tenses (Present, Past, Future – Simple & Continuous)
Fill in the correct tense:
✅ Present Simple: She _______ (handle) customer queries efficiently.
✅ Present Continuous: I _______ (work) on the quarterly report.
✅ Past Simple: We _______ (complete) the project last week.
✅ Past Continuous: She _______ (prepare) the slides when the meeting started.
✅ Future Simple: They _______ (finalize) the budget tomorrow.
✅ Future Continuous: I _______ (present) the report at 3 PM.
________________________________________
5. Articles (A, An, The)
Fill in the blanks with A, An, or The:
✅ I need _______ laptop for work.
✅ She gave me _______ update on the project.
✅ We scheduled _______ meeting for Monday.
________________________________________
6. Prepositions (in, on, at, by, for, etc.)
Choose the correct preposition:
✅ The meeting is _______ 2 PM.
✅ The files are _______ the shared folder.
✅ She is working _______ the new project.
✅ We need to submit the report _______ Friday.
________________________________________
7. Conjunctions & Linking Words
Fill in the correct conjunction:
✅ I will attend the meeting, _______ I have another call afterward.
✅ She completed the report _______ the manager requested it.
✅ We can either schedule the meeting today _______ postpone it to tomorrow.
________________________________________
8. Question Formation (Yes/No & WH-questions)
Complete the questions:
✅ Yes/No Questions:
•	_______ you complete the task? (Yes/No)
•	_______ the report ready? (Yes/No)
✅ WH-questions:
•	_______ time is the meeting?
•	_______ is the client presentation being held?
•	_______ was the project delayed?
✅ Polite Office Questions:
•	_______ you please send me the report?
•	_______ I schedule a meeting for tomorrow?
________________________________________
Answers:
1.	Parts of Speech:
✅ Noun: The meeting was scheduled for tomorrow.
✅ Verb: She sent the email before leaving the office.
✅ Adjective: We need a detailed report on the client’s feedback.
✅ Adverb: He completed the task quickly.
✅ Preposition: The documents are on the table.
✅ Conjunction: I wanted to finish the report on time, but I was interrupted.
✅ Pronoun: She will review the contract before signing.
2.	Basic Sentence Formation:
✅ Simple Sentence: The team submitted the new project.
✅ Compound Sentence: The meeting started late, but we still finished on time.
✅ Complex Sentence: Since the deadline is near, we need to work harder to complete the work.
3.	Subject-Verb Agreement:
✅ The manager approves the budget.
✅ The employees attend training every week.
✅ Everyone in the office is working hard.
4.	Tenses:
✅ She handles customer queries efficiently.
✅ I am working on the quarterly report.
✅ We completed the project last week.
✅ She was preparing the slides when the meeting started.
✅ They will finalize the budget tomorrow.
✅ I will be presenting the report at 3 PM.
5.	Articles:
✅ I need a laptop for work.
✅ She gave me an update on the project.
✅ We scheduled the meeting for Monday.
6.	Prepositions:
✅ The meeting is at 2 PM.
✅ The files are in the shared folder.
✅ She is working on the new project.
✅ We need to submit the report by Friday.
7.	Conjunctions:
✅ I will attend the meeting, but I have another call afterward.
✅ She completed the report because the manager requested it.
✅ We can either schedule the meeting today or postpone it to tomorrow.
8.	Question Formation:
✅ Yes/No Questions:
•	Did you complete the task? (Yes/No)
•	Is the report ready? (Yes/No)
✅ WH-questions:
•	What time is the meeting?
•	Where is the client presentation being held?
•	Why was the project delayed?
✅ Polite Office Questions:
•	Could you please send me the report?
•	May I schedule a meeting for tomorrow?


